parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger window actuator can cause the window to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to open or close, which can be a safety concern and a nuisance to the driver and passenger.
symptoms: The front passenger window will not open or close
the window makes a cracking noise when attempting to open or close.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning actuator can cause loud clicking noises, which can be a distraction to the driver and a nuisance to the occupants.
symptoms: Loud clicking noise from the passenger front side when the air conditioning is set below 72 degrees
the noise lasts for about 1 minute before going away.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can cause a safety concern, as the driver may not be able to alert other drivers or pedestrians in emergency situations.
symptoms: The horn fails to respond when engaged
the wires connected to the horn need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's inability to shift out of park can cause safety risks, such as being stuck in traffic or unable to move in emergency situations, and may lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle randomly gets stuck in park
unable to shift into gear when stationary
and may be accompanied by issues with the brake switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake switch recall issue can cause the vehicle to get stuck in park, leading to safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle gets stuck in park
unable to shift into gear when stationary
and may be accompanied by issues with the brake switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The exposed tailpipe can cause severe burns to individuals who come into contact with it, especially when loading or unloading cargo from the rear of the vehicle. This can lead to serious injuries, including second-degree burns, and potentially even infections.
symptoms: Burns on the leg or calf
typically in a crescent moon shape
with possible blistering and risk of infection.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent brake pedal sinking can cause reduced braking effectiveness, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal begins to brake at its normal pressure point and then sinks to the floor with reduced braking effect
resulting in a sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air in the ABS Control Module
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Air in the ABS control module can cause intermittent brake pedal sinking, leading to reduced braking effectiveness and increased risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal begins to brake at its normal pressure point and then sinks to the floor with reduced braking effect
resulting in a sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty HCU lines can cause air to enter the brake system, leading to intermittent brake pedal sinking and reduced braking effectiveness, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal begins to brake at its normal pressure point and then sinks to the floor with reduced braking effect
resulting in a sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lifters or Hydraulic Lash Adjusters Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lifters or hydraulic lash adjusters can cause engine noise, decreased engine performance, and potentially lead to engine damage.
symptoms: Rattling or tapping noise from the engine
typically at low engine speeds (around 1200 RPM) or when driving uphill
engine misfires
decreased engine performance
decreased fuel efficiency.
